'''Nicole Daedone''' is the founder and CEO of [[OneTaste]], the author of ''Slow Sex: the art and craft of the female orgasm'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Health/slow-sex-practice-promises-female-orgasm-15-minutes/story?id=14100270 |title=Slow Sex Practice Promises Female Orgasm in 15 Minutes That Lasts for Months |publisher=ABC News |date=2011-07-19 |accessdate=2014-06-25}}</ref> and a [[TED (conference)|TEDx]] speaker.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tedxtalks.ted.com/video/TEDxSF-Nicole-Daedone-Orgasm-Th |title=Watch "TEDxSF - Nicole Daedone - Orgasm: The Cure for Hunger in the Western Woman" Video at TEDxTalks |publisher=Tedxtalks.ted.com |date=2011-06-13 |accessdate=2014-06-25}}</ref> She teaches a practice called Orgasmic Meditation - a pathway to what in scientific literature is described as ''expanded orgasm''.<ref name="Sayin, Umit, December 2012">For example, as defined in: {{closed access}} {{cite journal| title=Doors of Female Orgasmic Consciousness: New Theories on the Peak Experience and Mechanisms of Female Orgasm and Expanded Sexual Response |last=Sayin |first=Umit |journal=[[NeuroQuantology]] | url=https://search.proquest.com/openview/c64ed5beab480fccd50e7e167065d7d0/1?pq-origsite=gscholar&cbl=2035897 | access-date=2017-09-07 |date=December 2012 |volume=V. 10 |issue=4 |pages=692–714 |subscription=yes |oclc=823076685 |issn=1303-5150}}</ref> Her academic background had been semantics<ref>{{cite web|author=Mary Spicuzza |url=http://www.sfweekly.com/2007-04-04/news/sex-and-sensuality/ |title=Sex and Sensuality |publisher=SF Weekly |date=2007-04-04 |accessdate=2014-06-25}}</ref> studied with teachers of yoga, [[Kabbalah]], and Buddhist meditation, and with Ray Vetterlein, who was in turn inspired by [[Lafayette Morehouse|Morehouse]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Brown|first1=Patricia Leigh|last2=Pogash|first2=Carol|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/03/15/fashion/15commune.html?_r=0|title=The Pleasure Principle|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2009-03-13}}</ref>
Daedone was born in [[Los Gatos, California]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Spicuzza|first1=Mary|title=Sex and Sensuality|url=http://www.sfweekly.com/content/printVersion/515940|accessdate=6 September 2014|work=SF Weekly|date=4 April 2007|archiveurl=http://www.rigorousintuition.ca/board2/viewtopic.php?f=8&t=23674&view=previous|archivedate=13 June 2009}}</ref> and has a Bachelor's degree in Gender Communications from [[San Francisco State University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Nicole Daedone|url=http://www.wishsummit.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1977:bio-nicole-daedone&catid=77|website=WishSummit.com|accessdate=6 September 2014}}</ref>
